<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99600050823697></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99600050823697><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=99600050823697>RE: Rating posts</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=67705><span id=Sage>Kensuke</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>72 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 24th 2:48 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It depends on the reason you're getting the Sarnak Enforcer. <br><br>If you're getting it solely to increase your 1HB skill, which is what I'm assuming, I'd suggest putting it in your primary, as it will be used on every attack, and therefore have a better chance of bumping up the skill. <br><br>However, the strategy I took to raise my 1HB skill was to buy an Enforcer (got one at around level 15 or so) and stick another blunt weapon in the secondary slot, whatever's available. I think I used a splintering club. This way, my 1HB skill increased extremely fast, and I had it maxxed out within about three bubbles of experience. <br><br>My hand-to-hand skill lagged out during those three bubbles, but it wasn't anything that couldn't be gotten back by using purely fists. In fact, I still use this technique. <br><br>I use my fist for primary, and an Essence of Dol in secondary. If I notice that my hand-to-hand is maxxed out, while my 1HB has only bumped up once or twice, I'll equip a 1HB in my primary until my 1HB skill is maxxed out, and then unequip it. However, I don't suggest you do this if you solo, as you won't be doing as much damage output. If you're in a group, the lack of damage is barely noticeable, and if things should get hairy in a battle with a group, you can always unequip the primary blunt mid-battle. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
