	   <tr><td colspan=2>On the topic of Special Attacks, see brother Kensukes post under the heading "Skills" below. Says everything that needs to be said.<br><br>As for 2hb, yes they are generally heavy. This isn't that big a problem at lvl 6, but still. Keep the skill up, it will definitely pay off. Until you get something half decent for practicing 2hb, just have some old worn Greatstaff or a similar item in your bank, and take it out when you hit a new level. It doesn't take that long to get the 5 skill-ups you can get with each new level, and then you can just stick it back in the vault and forget about it.<br><br>Also, it is no big deal if you are busy and miss practicing for a level or two, just don't neglect the skill. You probably won't be using high-end 2hb weapons for many levels still.<br><br>Welcome, new monk! Hope you will have as much fun as the rest of us!<br><br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk, Povar-Tarew Artisans, Xev.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
