<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9956565716612></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9956565716612><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=9956565716612>RE: Weight</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>192 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 20th 3:16 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.61]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nah, Monk doesn't have to be a twink class.  I started EQ with a monk, and haven't made an alt other than for banking and trading, and I'm doing fine.  I got a little help from friends when I got in my teens, but not anything too crazy, and in any case I did my first dozen or so levels by saving coppers and running to the bank a lot.  You will be overweight at lower levels, and it won't be that big a deal.  Past your first few levels, weight does start to be an issue - you can't buy enough AC gear to make up for losses from being overweight.  Part of the charm and challenge of the class is managing weight.  People who don't want to deal with that should just become warriors.  Cured silk is great stuff and will suit you fine for a long time.  Start with full cured silk, or Wu's if your tailoring is good enough, and a pair of gem inlaid gauntlets, if you want to have a good setup from the get-go.  As you level up and earn cash, upgrade piece by piece.<br><br>A full set of cured silk, a Sarnak enforcer (1.5 lbs) at 50 pp, Gem Inlaid Gauntlets (1.0) at 100 pp, and some jewelry (whatever u can afford) and you'll be well under limit.  Bags are an issue - Don't know if they nerfed them since, but I used medicine bags at 0.4 lbs each when I was young, instead of dealing with backpacks at 3.0 lbs.  Don't expect to carry more than two or three containers and stay under weight.  I still only carry 3 containers:  a Tink bag (1.0, 10 slot, 100%) a Shralok Pack (0.4, 8 slot, 25%) and a Dusty Ransacker's Pack (0.4, 8 slot, 25%).<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 49th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
