	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jul 21st 2:15 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a good alternative at lower levels to the expensive containers Keyeluke mentions, try some of the smaller tailored bags. These have 4-6 slots with a 10% weight-reduction, a weight of 0.3 to 0.8 themselves, and are available for 3-5 plat each.<br><br>Most tailors never make these, but with the recent changes (nerfings) to the containers, many monks are looking for an alternative to their now 10 times heavier sewing kits. The most dificult one of these trivials at 42, so making these yourself is also an option. Check here for further info:<br><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_tailoring.htm" target=_new>http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_tailoring.htm</a><br><br>-Incidently: Always go here for questions related to trades. By far the best site there is.<br><br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Un-Twinked monk of Cazic Thule<br>Povar-Tarew Artisans, Xev Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
