<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99562913795465></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99562913795465><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=99562913795465>RE: looking forward...</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>192 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 20th 7:38 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.61]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye, first order of business is to get a Fighting Baton if you don't already have one.<br><br>As for armor, I'm a believer in getting items that will last you a long time.  You don't list shoulders - look to get a Drolvarg Mantle.  You'll use it till your 50s.  Split-paw mask for the face is cheap, gives some light (if ya need it) and will do you for a while.  I second the Jagged Band recommendation (they're 5AC +3 str btw).  The Exe hood will do ya till you can get a froggy crown.<br><br>I disagree with serp bracers - I'm convinced now that pure stat gear is junk.  Vox bracers (assuming you're human) go for the same price, give you 6 more AC, and some cold resist.<br><br>As for the rest...  Some people are good horse-traders - if you can flip things well and for a profit, then upgrade everywhere you can, even a little bit.  If you're like me, and don't like to spend too much time selling, then forego the small upgrades (like CS to Wu's), and save your money till you can get what seems to be the standard mid-range monk items (posted all over this board).<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 49th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
