<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99562372797396></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99562372797396><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=99562372797396>Oasis to Overthere and back again.</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=57570><span id=Scholar>Niteklaw</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>49 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 20th 6:08 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've been this way quite a few times, and here is how you do it (and why you should do it this way...)<br><br>From Oasis to Overthere:<br>Get on the Raft from the Oasis. There are no guards or anything nasty here, so you're quite safe.<br>When arriving in Timorous Deep, the raft pauses for a while. If you are impatient and have clipping set to the max, you can get off and swim to the docks (Head for the Cliffs you see). Otherwise, the raft drops you off at the beach.<br>Follow the cliffs on your right to get to the docks, watching out for Ogres on the way. Alternatively, get back in the water and swim keeping the cliffs on your left, to avoid the Ogres all together.<br>There are TWO docks here. If you run, it's the RIGHT one, if you swim, it's the FIRST one.<br>Wait here, and the ship will come to take you on rather a long tour of Timorous Deep, before zoning into Overthere.<br>In The Overthere, swim for shore while the boat is waiting to dock unless you are very high level. Stay away from the buildings on the right.<br><br>From Overthere to Oasis:<br>DON'T use the docks in Overthere unless you are a high-leveller. They are filled with the undead. Follow the shore, with the sea on your right, until you get to the wall.<br>Swim around the wall and wait on the shore for the boat to dock.<br>AGAIN: Do NOT use the docks - Wait on the shore, within SIGHT of the docks.<br>When the boat has docked, swim out and board it from the FAR side, and you will be safe.<br>It can be difficult to board the ship when swimming, but go up one of the "slanted" barrels, using it as a little ramp.<br>The boat zones to Timorous Deep and docks on Ogre Island.<br>Run to the beach, keeping the cliffs on your LEFT side.<br>Alternatively, swim around the cliffs (Keeping them on your RIGHT) to avoid any Ogres that might be hanging around.<br>Wait on the beach for one of the small rafts to fetch you.<br>The raft zones to Oasis of Marr, and you get off.<br><br>-One general rule: If the boat has sailed, well, then the boat has sailed. Don't bother trying to swim after it to catch it...you can't, and if you could, it would be very difficult to board it. You will most likely just look stupid, get lost and drown.<br><br>And that, ladies and gentlemen, is "Crossing Timorous Deep for Dummies". Thank you, thank you, be sure to tip your waitress.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
